# Generated from codex-contract.toml. Do not edit directly.

Never run destructive git commands such as `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fd`, or `git checkout --` unless the user explicitly asks.
Never push or merge automatically.
Do not implement new feature work directly on the main workspace.
Follow the project quality pipeline: explore, plan, critique, implement, test, review, verify, then optional human merge approval.
Read-only local inspection commands are allowed when needed to understand, validate, or test the workspace.
